                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/808.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 19, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Archbishop will resign the presidency probably Tuesday or Wednesday of next
                    week, according to information received this morning from his brother, Secretary
                    Nouel, who desires me to have an <pb facs="0525" n="421" xml:id="pg_421"/>
                    additional gunboat at this capital for moral effect. I have consulted with the
                    commander of the <hi rend="italic">Wheeling</hi> and we conclude that it is
                    advisable to have a second gunboat within call, preferable at Mayaguez or in
                    Samaná Bay, since the cutting of the telegraph lines across the island will
                    probably be the first act of any new revolution.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
